      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Afrika Islam''' (born Charles Glenn, 1968, [[New York City]]) also known as the &quot;''Son of [[Afrika Bambaataa|Bambaataa]]''&quot;, is an American [[hip hop production|hip-hop producer]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.thedjlist.com/djs/AFRIKA_ISLAM/ |title=Afrika Islam |publisher=thedjlist.com |accessdate=2009-07-21}}&lt;/ref&gt;

==Life==
In the 1980s he moved to [[Los Angeles]] where he co-produced [[Ice T]]'s early albums ''[[Rhyme Pays]]'' and ''[[Power (Ice T album)|Power]]''.
In the late 1990s, Afrika Islam joined German [[techno music|techno]] icon [[Westbam]] to form [[Mr. X and Mr. Y]], a techno duo that made commercial techno with [[Electro (music)|Electro]] influences.

